      "solution": "def collatz(n):\n    steps = 0\n    maxi = n\n    while n > 1:\n        if n % 2 == 0:\n            n //= 2\n        else:\n            n = 3*n+1\n        steps += 1\n        maxi = max(maxi, n)\n    return steps, maxi\n\nN = int(input())\n\nfor _ in range(N):\n    print(*collatz(int(input())))\n",
      "statement": "The <<Collatz conjecture>> is one of the most famous unsolved problems in mathematics. The conjecture states that for any positive integer, its Collatz sequence (defined below) converges to {{1}}.\n\nYou are given a list of integers, and you must compute the <<total stopping time>> (ie. steps before reaching {{1}}) and the <<maximum reached>> in the Collatz sequence of that number.\n\n<<Mathematical information>>\nThe sequence is defined as such:\nGiven a strictly positive integer [[n]],\nIf [[n]] is even, the next term is [[n]]/2\nIf [[n]] is odd, the next term is 3*[[n]]+1",
